<Content>Very Pleased Stayed here because of the price, and was very reluctant after having read some of the reviews. Actually, I was SCARED after having read some of the reviews. We had stayed at this hotel when it used to be the Wyndham, and even before when it was the Doral.First check in was easy and fast. The bellman immediately had our luggage in our room and was very pleasant.We had a Junior Suite, and it was in excellent condition. There was no view, but we checked in late and were out fairly early, so the view was not an issue. The room was nicely decorated, bathroom in good condition, and the room was SPOTLESS!The TV was an old tube TV, and the room had no CD player, but for the price of $130, it could not be beat. Being from Miami originally, I knew the area and know the history of the hotels in the area. This hotel was built in the 60's, just as Miami's heyday was ending. Not far is the Fountainbleu and Eden Roc.This is not the South Beach area, and is loaded with condos and a much different scene than SoBe. Nonetheless, everything is still close by.The only complaint was check out, which if I had done the express checkout I would not have had anything to complain about. It was slow, very slow.All-in-all, a great stay and would definitely recommend to anyone! 
