<Content>good and Bad bits I was a little wary having read some of the reviews but overall it wasn't as bad as I had possibly expected.The room was fine. It was clean bright and comfortable which met our needs for the 4 night stay. We had a side room view, ovelooking the large condo next door with a side view of the beach and a side view of the waterway and city. It was cleaned daily with fresh towels, tea and coffee.The hotel itself is quite ornate and the reception area is quite elaborate, but the prices match. The in room mini bar is very expensive. my tip is to buy a few items from walmart or CVS in LIncoln road (snacks/ soft drinks etc)The restaurants are also expensive and the one meal we had in there on our first evening before we found our way around wasn't very good.As some have said the hotel has a nice setting but isn't near to anywhere else to eat or shop. We caught the bus across from the hotel to Lincoln road ( cost $2 each) and ate at a lovely restaurant called NEXXT. The choice was huge as were the portions so if you're not a big eater get a dish to share, staff will happily oblige.Lincoln road is very nice but I must say I felt a little uncomfortable, especially as the evening wore on as there seemed to be a lot of homeless- type people about rummaging in bins and begging on the streets, some right next to restaurants. not too different to most large cities both in the UK and abroad but a bit off putting none the less 
