<Author>CarolSkid
<Content>Brit View! So many reviews that are knocking the decor, saying it smells and that people are rude and unfriendly. My husband and myself started our holiday by staying in the Miami Beach resort for 4 nights.We caught a taxi from the airport which was a set fare of $33.50, which only took about 20mins. We were helped with our cases inside and checked in easily and quickly by smiling friendly staff. We weren't hassled in getting our cases to our 10th floor ocean facing room. Our room was clean, including the carpet and the bathroom and had no complaints about any smells - only good. Our maid was a lovely lady who greeted us each morning with a big smile and a 'Good Morning'. She cleaned and refreshed our bed sheets each day by the time we got back from breakfast.We had breakfast in the Seabreeze, however we felt the buffet was just too much to eat, and opted for the option of two eggs plus bacon/sausage with potatoes and toast, with endless coffee. This costed around $14 each. We never felt like eating then until the night.We spent time around the pool, and no matter what time was able to get a bed with a fluffy clean towel. If you are there over a wekend they have live music in the afternoon. Each day they come around with complimentary cold flannels and fresh fruit. We overlooked the pool and each morning around 7.30am we saw it being cleaned and vaccumed.The beach is also cleaned and the walk into the sea was completely free of rocks and seaweed. We thoroughly enjoyed our dips in the sea.If you can tear yourself away from driving everywhere, then jump on the local bus that stops outside. We used it to get downtown, Ocean Drive, Lincoln Road, Bayside, basically everywhere. And all it cost us was $1.50 each!! We never felt threatened, actually the locals were very courteous and stood up for me to sit down.As tourists, naturally we went on the Duck Tour, which we really enjoyed - and yes we caught the bus there too!We took the opportunity to travel down the Florida Keys to Key West from Miami. We went by Greyhound bus, which took just 4 hours, and yes again much cheaper than hiring a car.We decide to have a security box, which we arranged with reception completely free.We came back to Miami Beach Resort for just one more night before we flew to New York, and again our room was clean and non smelly. Checking in and out again was quick and easy with smiling staff. We also saw the Salsa conference along with the Litino Aids conference, and caused us no problems whatsoever!! People just having a great time and bothering no one else.I've been called fussy in my time - but I would recommend this to any nationality. I can only speak as I find.Enjoy the Pina Colada's at the Beach bar - yummy with more than enough alcohol. 
