<Author>Hejnas
<Content>A Severe Letdown Upon arrival, I felt that the valets weren't very helpful or friendly, just there to do the bare minimum. The lobby area is gorgeous with Marble and wonderful decorations. Then we got in the elevators which are very old, unstable, shakey, and some grease managed to get on the door on the inside of the elevator. Then when we got off the elevator at our FIRST room, there was a strong, musty smell. After getting in our room, which was quite outdated, we could only take so much of the smell. It was strong of Mildew as if a pipe had burst and was never cleaned properly. We went to the front desk to voice our problem in which we were put into another room. We decided to take our own luggage to that room only to find that when we got into it, there was no comforter on the bed, the chair was much older than the other and had several rips in it. The bed had no bedding on it, the padding on the iron was barely dangling on as if it had been ripped off and then just tossed back on. So we went back down to the front and once again voiced our problems. Our third room was decent, except for the lack of a comforter and chipping paint so we decided to take that one. BEWARE of the sauna in the gym because the metal nails are exposed (either wood nails should have been used or nailed/screwed from the bottom up) and needless to say both my girlfriend and I burnt ourselves. The gym was nice, with 2 stories. We then jumped in the pool only to find gum in there, part of someones weave at the bottom, and a huge rust stain on the side of the pool. Now all they have to do is drain the pool, sand and spackle, a 2 day job at most. We also looked at the building itself from the outside only to notice how old it looked and how there was rust all over the place. So that night we went back after dinner(off site) and went right to bed. I didn't look at the sheets to see the yellow stains that I discovered the following morning. Then when I went to take a shower the drain was clogged. So I called down to have both problems resolved. A few minutes later 5 workers entered the room 2 for the bathroom, 2 for the bed and a supervisor. As I pointed the stains to the housekeeper, they both looked at me like i was crazy. So then they cleared the bed and began to put on new sheets. When my girlfriend pointed out that there were the same yellow stains on the new sheets, the housekeepers both sighed deeply as if it were a hassle to do their job, cleared the bed and put other sheets on the bed. The entire time they were speaking in a different language, possibly and alternative dialect of Spanish and the whole conversation was quite loud and we both felt was aimed at us as we sat in the chair watching television. We dined at the breakfast place at the bottom by the pool which was quite nice and the service was good in that area. The wedding reception for my friend was nice, i like the setup they had on the top floor. The food was quite good and the view and room were quite nice. The next morning we woke up and called down for a late check out of noon which we were granted. Minutes later there was a housekeeper knocking at the door. As we tried to explain to her several times that we had a late checkout, she was quite rude and not understanding of the situation. When we left breifly to return my tuxedo down the hall to my friends room, the housekeeper was almost right outside our room, waiting. She immediately asked if we were checking out and once again we told her not until noon. We returned the tuxedo and then as we walked back down the hall she basically just watched us. We felt quite uncomfortable, packed our items and then left immediately. Now we explained all of this and we had some things credited back to us and then one of the ladies at the front desk asked us if we were used to staying at 5 star properties and not 3 stars. I told her that I work in the industry and that we have stayed at all kinds of hotels. She then just gave us an odd look and continued to do her work. I understand that they are not a 5 star property, but most of these things are unacceptable, I wouldn't have tolerated it there, just like I wouldn't tolerate it at my own job, or at a Homewood suites, or a Fairfield Inn, or a Motel 6. This is not a 3 star resort, maybe a 2....maybe. It has a great location by the beach in a good area of Miami but the hotel and most of the service is pitiful. It has so much potential just due to the location. If a company were willing to pay to refurbish, repair, partially restaff, reorganize and redecorate, they would have a gold mine. 
