<Author>Seetheworld00
<Content>What Happened???!?? OK. I am an avid trip advisor reader. I always read reviews from this website before I stay anywhere. Even if I have been to the hotel before. I like to stay abreast of the situation. Things change you know? Anyways I stayed at the Miami Beach Resort and Spa when it was actually the Wyndham Resort and Spa a few years back. Back then they were giving you free wine and cheese in your room when you check in. It was much cleaner. Over the years new owners took over and the hotel became the Miami Beach Resort Spa. It was then things changed. Overall the outside decor of the hotel as well as the lobby area looks lavish and inviting. I will attach pictures later. But when you get upstairs to the rooms, they are a bit disappointing. The color scheme is not very inviting. The first couple of times I stayed in a standard double bed room and was OK with the results. This year, I rented a Junior Suite with two double beds. the junior suite was an exact replica of the standard room for the exception of a teensy bit more space for a sofa and a coffee table. It didnt remind me of a suite at all. Not to mention we did not get the double beds we asked for. We got one king sized bed. It was four women in a junior suite with one king sized bed, and a pull out sofa. Lets be real. In some hotels the bathroom sink and vanity area is separate from the bath and shower area. In this suite, the bathroom was all in one. Meaning if you closed the door for privacy everyone else would have to wait for you to finish out the bathroom in order to maybe use the sink to brush your teeth or wash your face. Remember, I shared this suite with four women. I shudder to see what the penthouse suite looks like. Moving on. When we [--] and moaned to the front desk about our meager accommodations they offered us two roll-a-way beds free of charge and a free day of a complimentary buffet breakfast at the hotel's hibiscus restaurant on the lower level. Now the buffet is 19.99 per person. It was good I will not lie. But 20.00 for a buffet breakfast? A little steep. Furthermore I think we should've gotten breakfast for free our entire stay seeing as how we were inconvenienced. But that didn't happen. The management team told us that double beds are not guaranteed. So I asked him. Why would the reservation specialist ask me what kind of beds we wanted if it wasn't guaranteed? Eric ( was his name) told me that they don't guarantee the bed type and that it's just a courtesy to the customer, to be asked as a preference. A preference? Isn't preference what you want? And doesn't a person asking you what your preference is constitute you getting what you want? I don't know, that sounded like a crock of [--] to me. Moving on. We had to suffer with the roll-a-way beds and make due. Everything you order at this hotel is stamped with an 18% service charge. That's fine. Most hotel's do this. However, if I am going to pay 18% for you to pour me a glass of orange juice then disappear after that, I am at some point going to feel jerked around. This is what happens at the buffet breakfast. The waiters automatically charge an 18% service charge to your bill because they bring you coffee, tea, or water, which is included in the buffet price. So why do we need them to pour our beverages? It adds an air of elegance I suppose. However after you get your beveraged poured for you for 18% extra charge added to your bill, they disappear into the kitchen and you never see them again until you are ready to leave. Fascinating stuff huh? Trust me, everything I am writing is not biased. THis is nothing but the truth. Moving on. The pool area is sufficient. However, I would have preferred they clean it at some point during our 4 night stay. They did not. So if a child pissed in the pool, someone had snot nosed boogers floating around in the pool, you got it on you. I was not pleased with that. Pools should be sparkling and clean. After a couple of days, this pool was a bit murky which meant it needed to be cleaned. A shower afterwards is a must. The chairs around the pool were sufficient as were towels. I was completely satisfied with the cabana by the pool and the employees that worked there. They went out of there way to make sure we were accommodated. They also gave us free refills on all carbonated soda beverages. The beach water in Miami is always beautiful to look at if you are like me from New York, and all the water here looks gray. However, there are thousands of rocks in this water near the shore so pls be careful. I scraped my feet dozens of times. If you want to rent a jet ski it was 75 for one person 80.00 for two people for a half hour ride. Not bad, but once you get on not nearly enough time. Once you get over your fear of all that open water you start having fun and its time to come back to shore. Recommend an hour. However the price is like 150.00. Way too expensive. If you travel to another beach in Florida,close by you can find a better deal. Getting back to the hotel. It's right on the beach so once you walk past the pool area, you are on the beach. Housekeeping was very efficient in bringing us what we asked for in a timely fashion. They were also very nice and did so with a smile. Never order food from the menus placed in your room. The food from these outside places suck and you never know what you will get when they deliver. TRUST ME! Never buy anything from the hotel gift shop, They overcharge for the simplest of items. Just go down the street to the Walgreens or CVS and save some money. The guys that take your bags to your room are nice enough. Although be prepared to tip because they will stand and wait for it. We hated our room, but all other features of the hotel were satisfactory. This was our third time staying here, and this was the worse visit we had thus far.The last two times our rooms were spotless for standard booking. We were terribly disappointed with the junior suite. Don't get sucked in to reserve this type of room. We won't be staying here again. I think a hotel review should comprise mainly of how you felt about the room you stayed in. Overall we were not happy. One more positive I can say about the hotel is the location. It's about 10-15 minutes away from South Beach nightlife so if you want to relax and max out with out all the fuss, this is a great location for some true peace and quiet. I will be heading off to Cancun next, to review another hotel. Stay tuned and I will let you know what to expect! Safe Travels! LaToya 
