<Content>Half good-Half bad I booked thru hotwire, which I always use and never have had a problem. Since you do not know where you are staying I could not check until after I was already booked. The reviews here are terrifying. When I arrived they could not find my reservation, it took them 45 minutes. I had to call hotwire twice, they finally said we have you in our reservation dept. but it's not yet in this system (the front desk) so I still had to wait. Mind you my two kids are screaming running around the freaking lobby acting like they never do. So I'm really aggravated, finally they say we have your reservation but now I have to find you a room. I was livid and hating myself for booking thru Hotwire. They also wanted me to give a $50.00 deposit which was refundable, when I asked where was that in writing the manager gave the nod to proceed. So I did not give a deposit.From what I read I thought the room was going to be disgusting and it wasn't. It was pretty decent for the price. The bathroom was updated, but the tile in the shower was filthy with grime. I wonder if they've heard of Tilex? The hotel overall needs an update, but it's not horrible. The pool area was great. My 4 year old loved the kiddy pool and it was good for me b-cuz I could sort of relax. The beach access was the reason we booked here. For the price staying on the beach seemed impossible for the high prices, so we booked at $89.What you need to take into consideration is the $22.00 parking. I thought it was bull to charge additionally. You are really paying $111.00 plus 10.00 resort fee plus tax.We are locals and took our kids for a Spring Break mini vacation, that's why we wanted pool and beach. For that purpose it worked. The restaurants are ridiculous in pricing; there is nothing in walking distance so research the places that deliver in the area before. If not you have to cab it or pay $22.00 again. The pool had music. They do not allow coolers or for you to eat anything that is not their food. If you have kids you know you need snacks. I refuse to pay $10.00 for a juice. We had to go eat at the beach and hide our coolers. The staff was alright, some made pervy remarks when I walked by in my bathing suit. I did not know if I should be flattered or insulted? Overall I don't think it was as bad as the other reviews. It has the plus of the beach access. They could work on the parking prices, cleanliness and food prices. They did have a kid鈥檚 breakfast menu which was sort of cheap. 4 mini pancakes for $3.00 that was good because we were worried about breakfast. The adults is stupid! $20.00 for eggs and ham and potatoes! Something cheap to entertain the kids it will work. Something nice classy chic it will not work. Good Luck! 
