<Content>Not worth the money- anything but glamorous Our stay at the Miami Beach resort and spa was unsatisfactory at best. It started at check in. There were 4 girls staying in this suite so we paid an extra $80 to ensure we would have 2 double beds. We checked in, went up to the room to find the door propped open (creepy) and what do you know.................1 king....for 4 people!!! We spent the first 30 minutes of our vacation, on the phone(which was in the bathroom???), filing a complaint. They were completly booked so they sent us 2 roll-a ways and took of the extra $80 charge, dropping our nightly room rate to $375/night. The room was also very plain and not what I expected for paying over $400/ night. Also, the window was broken but we had a great view of the pool and the beach. We went out Friday night and woke up bright and early Saturday morning because the sun and heat was beating in through the massive, curtainless window in the living room (which was where we had to sleep because we had one king and 2 roll-a ways). Whatever, we didnt come to Miami to sleep so we headed to the pool to soak some rays. Around lunch time we headed to the pool bar to get a snack. We all ordered the exact same thing and got 4 different bills (amounts) We spoke to the manager and he fixed it but that was also wierd and wasted our vacation time. So the 4 of us finished our afternoon and headed upstairs to get ready for dinner and another night out. Hot, tired and sunburned we make it back to the suite,stick the key in the door and it doesnt work. We have to go back downstairs to the service desk and wait in line and get the key reprogramed.(happened 3 times throughout the stay) Not that big of a deal, however, it was another inconvience. We get ready to shower and flip the switch in the bathroom and the lightbulb burnt out! So again, we called the service desk and they were going to send someone up to fix it immediatly. So we waited and an hour passes and no one has shown up. So we started showering, in the dark, because we were going to be late for our dinner reservation. Another half hour passes and someone knocks on the door. The maintence man shows up to change the bulb, however, he brings the absolute wrong bulb so he leaves. We are blow drying, strightening hair and the circut breaker blew (no power). Again we call the front desk (from the bathroom, in the dark) and I think you get the picture. When we finally spoke to the manager he was nice and apologized for all the inconviences we had encountered but for me, the experience with this hotel was not pleasant. We spent a lot of our vacation/relaxation time fixing things that we should not have had to worry about. The majority of the staff was unfriendly and unhelpful, with the exception of Patricia (bartender) and Derek (bell hop), those 2 employees were extremely helpful and nice. This hotel has the potential to be a very nice place but they need to get it together. I will NOT stay there again!!! 
