<Content>What a great place! My husband and I just returned from a 5 night stay at The Miami Beach Resort and Spa. What a wonderful getaway! We wanted to go some place warm yet stay in the United States. We couldn't have picked a better place to go. The hotel is beautiful. The entrance and lobby was very elegant, it made you feel special just walking in! Our room was on the 10th floor. While our room did not over look the ocean which I'm sure was a beautiful view, we did over look the intercoastal waterway and the city. At one point during our stay we considered asking if we could be moved to an ocean view but decided against it because we loved the view we had! The room itself was very comfortable, well maintained. Our maid (not sure of her name) did a great job getting our room ready before we returned from the pool - the room always looked great! Breakfast each morning was at the Hibiscus Court. You could order from the menu or choose the buffet, both were equally good, the service was wonderful. George, our waiter was very friendly, attentive and took great care of us.  The time we spent at the pool each day was very relaxing. It was a beautiful setting with palm trees, tropical foliage and just a few steps away was the beach.  We made our way to the Seabreeze Bar and Grill each day, which was poolside, where we had the pleasure of being taken care of by three of the best bartenders you'll come across - Elke, Zinna, and David. All three were fun to talk with, and made delicious drinks, the food there was very good as well! Another plus to this hotel are the shops on the lower lobby. The three shops had very nice selections to choose from so we chose from all three! We spent quite a bit of time at Southbeach which was so much fun! Lots to see and experience - good food, good shopping, good people watching!  I would definitely recommend this hotel to anyone. Every aspect of our stay was truly wonderful from check in to check out! We can't wait to go back!! 
