<Author>lfalcon05
<Content>It was OK I booked this hotel thru their main company website (LXR). We stayed over the Thanksgiving holiday. I researched many many hotels and resorts in Miami beach and read many reviews. I was very concerned that this hotel would not be ok.It was OK. Not great but not as bad as some make it out to be - there are however problems. I booked a fall in love package thru the main website (they are owned by LXR) and the package included breakfast, an oceanview room with King and a bottle of champagne. I called the hotel to make sure that it would be accomodated that way and they assured me it would. When i arrived though, they had me booked into a room with two double beds (kinda hard for romance??) and the champagne was not there. I did however explain that I called and insisted that i get a king etc. The breakfast coupons were also not there but they managed after a few phone calls to get us everything we needed. - the problem is the hotel doesnt know what the corporate packages even are!!The hotel is filled with Europeans that LOVE TO SMOKE and are extrememely rude. Thats no fault of the hotels though. I am spoiled coming from California where we have strict smoking laws. But unfortunately everyone smokes - by the pool in the restaraunts - everywhere -its horrible. One day at the pool i was sunbathing and these people in front of me decided they needed shade so they put their umbrella up - and it covered me not them! I moved to another spot thinking at some point they might apologize but they didnt. And then to make matters worse they lite up the cigs. UGH... The rooms are ok, they need to be updated and there is no light in the shower so its kinda dark and hard to see. But its a big room with a lot of closet space and two sinks which is helpful for getting ready. Our maid left a lot to be desired in terms of cleanliness, I dont think she cleaned our toilet the whole time we were there - which for the money - I think she should - she basically made the bed and left towels and emptied the garbage. The view was nice - we were on the 6th floor - in the middle.The staff of the hotel was pleasant enough. The valet treated us well. You pay for parking everywhere, at every hotel and this one was no exception. $22 a day. Plus we tipped the valet. I noticed that the Europeans did not tip - and we ALWAYS got our car first. They know who treats them well and who doesnt.The only other downside was the breakfast - it was a buffet. Which was fine, but the wait staff - when they knew you had a coupon did NOT treat you well. One day in particular a new hostess was sitting us down and she screamed at us to give her the blue coupon?? I told her three times we dont have blue coupon, and she showed the coupon we had to one of the waiters and said something in spanish they shook their heads in DISGUST and sat us down. I was really upset and am going to write to the corporate office about the treatment. We went 4 days in a row, and each time we left a nice tip for them, thats the only time they said thanks - they assumed since its a free meal they dont get their usual 17 1/2 percent (its not free you pay extra for that in the package) but most dont tip on stuff like that (or so I heard and saw) ALSO gratuity is included at ALL restaurants so watch for that when signing your check.If you have already booked this hotel - dont despair, tip and complain nicely and they will help you. Unfortunately south beach miami is just really expensive and undergoing TONS of remodeling and new construction. I wont be going back. DONT go to Florida if you cant stand cigaretttes. Next time I think i ll stick with Hawaii. 
