<Content>Miami Beach Resort and Spa - a pleasant surprise I had booked my stay at the Miami Beach Resort and Spa through a booking service for the meeting I was attending. My choice was based on availability and price for the dates of the meeting. I was not enthusiastic about a meeting in Miami Beach, but my arrival at Miami Beach Resort and Spa changed my mind.From the time the shuttle dropped me off, to the time I checked out, all aspects of the stay rated 5 stars with me. From the moment I stepped out of the shuttle, everyone I came in contact with at the hotel went out of their way to be of service, and to help in any way possible. Everyone on staff that I ran into during my 5-night stay was genuinely friendly. They went out of their way to be helpful, whether it was directions to the beach or pool, recommendations for places to eat in the area, or providing menus for places that would deliver food when I was too tired to go out. If they saw me looking confused, whoever passed by would offer to help.I was allowed to check in early, and the room was beautiful, very bright and cheery, with great views of the ocean and the Miami skyline (beautiful at night). I hated to ever leave the room.As an early riser, I was impressed by the cheerfulness of the staff in the Hibiscus room, and the way they remembered me from morning to morning, including all my individual preferences. They were the best. And the poolside/ocean view outside dining area was perfect for those hot afternoons.As I said earlier, I had dreaded the trip to Miami Beach, hearing only negative things from people who had gone there before. If they had stayed at the Miami Beach Resort and Spa, I'm convinced they would have had a much better report. Of the 9 staff from my business that attended this meeting, all stayed in different hotels. From all reports, I stayed in the best hotel. I would consider going back to Miami Beach, and that's something I never thought I would say. Kay 
