<Author>nyxplant
<Content>Nice value, great experience, does need some updating though... This hotel is definitely getting a bad rap on here. I don't know what other folks are experiencing, but our experience was most positive.I was concerned, too, because of all the rants that have been written. I was so concerned that I contacted the Wyndham prior to arriving to seek assurance that we were going to be satisfied. Well, satisfy they did - and then some. The front desk manager personally responded to my email and reassured us that while the hotel is in need of some (upcoming) renovations, it is in no way in such a state as some of these reviews would have you believe. The rooms are outdated a bit - the tile is old, as are the carpets. The hotel will tell you this, if you ask. I think the rates reflect this. You can get some pretty discounted rates for this property.Also contrary to some reviews, they DO participate in the ByRequest program (frequent travelers program) and you'll receive your upgrade, welcome drinks, newspapers, etc. Another myth debunked. The bedding was all fairly new - not stained or old as some have suggested. Actually the beds were very comfortable and the sheets very crisp.The most noticeable areas in need of improvement are definitely the bathrooms - the grout is stained (clean, but stained) and there is some corrosion on some of the fixtures - but then again, it's 50 years old...so it's in relatively good condition for that age. It wasn't such an issue that we thought to even complain, however. It was as they had informed us.The elevators were slow at times - and a few didn't always seem to respond to the button requests - I don't know why...but they were generally responsive and not too bad.As for the purported rudeness, we experienced exactly the opposite - outstanding, friendly, over-the-top service. David at the pool bar stayed open more than 2 hours after close to serve the people who were still having fun...Lillian (?) in the Hibiscus restaurant serving us great fresh squeezed orange juice...Dawkins the bell hop who took us to our room and was just so friendly...Arris who let us park our car in the front for a little while when we just wanted to run in for a few minutes...Estela (?) at the pool who comes around with complimentary apples, orange slices, pina coladas and lots more while you're lounging around the pool. The pool staff does a wonderful job of keeping the pool area clean and neat. Dina (?) was just so nice and friendly while we were down there.Lastly, Stacey - the front desk manager, was the sweetest of all, responding to our email concerns - calling us personally in our room to make sure everything to our satisfaction - and personally checking us out upon our departure. We couldn't have been more pleased.The property's location on the beach is perfect. Great sandy beaches and soft sand bars to walk out onto. The boardwalk is just down the beach two doors and it's a beautiful evening stroll. The sand is groomed every morning by a beachcombing bulldozer crew - keeping it nice and trash free.The food in the hotel was very good. Great buffet breakfeasts and very nice dinners overlooking the pool.This is not a 5 star hotel - although it will be after the renovations are complete. But it is, in my opinion, worth the rates that they charge. Don't believe the rants - this place is very nice. I've found in my travels that people will treat you in similar ways that you treat them. Perhaps some of the folks had some bona fide bad experiences, but I would guess that quite a few were being quite demanding of this place and expecting luxuries that they are not able to provide. I would encourage you to contact the front desk prior to arriving to talk to them about the room and your expectations so that there are no surprises when you arrive. If I can be of any help, please feel free to contact me.Bon voyage! 
