<Content>Pretty Good We stayed at the Wyndham Miami Beach for four nights from April 21-25. We had signed up for their Wyndham by Request just days before and for that trouble we had wine, cheese and crackers waiting in our room upon arrival. Sign-up, if you can. We requested and received a king room on a high floor and had a lovely view of the bay and ocean. The room was well kept, with a great mattress, spacious and had mondo closet space. The lighting in the bathroom was not good. The toiletries are top notch -- Golden Door. The pool was nice and the lounges had thick padding on them by the pool. One morning they came by with fresh orange slices, cold water, and then popcicles, all free. The beach was lovely with lounges, but you had to pay if you wanted an umbrella. There's a boardwalk about 100 yards towards South Beach that will take you almost all the way there. We walked it one day and it took about 30-40 minutes. For those who need to be in the action, this is not it. For those who like a little quiet, it's great. Plus, the bus takes you into South Beach for $1.25 and it's easy. We did this several times instead of getting the rental car out from the valet-only parking at the hotel which is pricey ($18/day) compared to other hotels. We walked to Eden Roc for coffee (Starbuck's) and pastries several mornings, but they have a little shop that's open in the mornings and sells coffee and pastries if you don't want the buffet breakfast also offered. Another reviewer said it was not a four-star but the best three-star ever. I'd say it's just shy of a proper four-star hotel, and if you booked a good rate, worth every penny. 
