<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>The wrong place to stay in this area Stayed at this resort for one night last night. This was our first experience in Miami, and we had a certificate for a free night at this hotel. Got to the hotel early in the day to be able to explore the beach area. Were told our room wasn't ready, and to come back later. They offered us a junior suite since I had enrolled in the Wyndham-By-Request online. Surprised by the fact there is only valet parking allowed, to the tune of $18 per day. We asked the valet to hold our car while we went to check-in, and came back and the car was already parked. We asked for the car and were given the attitude You don't need your car *already* do you? The valet advised walking the area would be fine. Since we didn't know the area, we took his word, and boy he couldn't have been more wrong!We ended up walking down the street and onto the boardwalk which headed south from the hotel. We wanted to check out South Beach, and ended up walking miles to get there. It had to be at least 3 or 4 miles until we even reached the edge of South Beach. It was at least 7 or 8 blocks from the hotel before there was *anything* to eat--- and dozens of blocks before anything decent.We went back to the hotel around 2 since this seemed like plenty of time to have a room ready (they weren't that busy.) By this time we were completely worn out from the now 8-9 mile hike. We were told again the room wasn't ready and to come back.After getting the car, and coming back twice after that, the room was finally ready at 5pm. (We had to get up at 4am the next morning for a flight.) We have never waited this long for a room to be ready.The suite was roomy, and there was a nice welcome package with cheese and crackers and the beverage we requested online. On the bad side, the suite was right on the elevators, so you could hear the elevator everytime it passed. Speaking of elevators, there aren't enough for the hotel, and in one the display doesn't even work to tell you which floor you were on. There was a shower, but no bathtub. We settled in, and being so put off by the valet staff and the walk earlier, we were hesitant to venture out again for dinner. We went to the concierge for a recommendation, but there were about a dozen people in line, and in 15 minutes of waiting, the line didn't move an inch. The hotel pushed a pizza special from room service --- which was a great price, but completely AWFUL pizza. It was *REALLY* bad.After going to bed hungry and exhausted, and waking to our 4am wake up call, there was absolutely no hot water in the room to take a shower. We had to take a cold shower and head to the airport for a full day of travel. We complained at check-out, and they removed the $10 per night resort fee and said they would see what they could do about the room service and parking fees.Overall we really weren't impressed. Even having the free night certificate didn't make up for the bad location, poor service, extra fees,  terrible room service. We wouldn't stay here again, and don't recommend it to anyone. There are plenty of other hotels in better locations with better service who will earn our money next time. 
