<Content>Wouldn't go back Service is not a strong point of this hotel. When we checked in they had given our non-smoking room away and tried to give us a smaller smoking room. We had to speak to 2 different managers to get the situation worked out and they acted as if they were doing us a favor. The hotel room was small and was not cleaned well on a daily basis. The elevators were constantly in repair, and the sundry shop is too small. The pool area is nice as is the beach, however there is nothing else to do. The hotel is not anywhere near tourist attractions or restaurants. The whole area is very expensive and you must either drive or take a taxi. When a hotel says it is a resort I expect that I would-in theory- never have to leave the grounds- not true with this place. 
