<Content>Liked it My wife and 3 year old son (his first plane ride) stayed at the Wyndam Miami Beach resort for four nights in early June of 03. I was impressed by the level of service and friendliness of the staff. The location on the Miami strip is ideal for families and anyone who is looking for some relaxation, while still only a few miles ($7-$9 taxi) from the action at South Beach. The pool and beach area was very nice. Pool bar a bit expensive ($8 drink $6 beer). The down side of this hotel is the lack of variety as far as evening dining. The website advertises 2 resturants in addition to the room service menu. What I found is for dinner ($16-$23 entree) we had one restaurant with a very limited menu (5 entrees), which was the same as the room service menu. If you call yourself a full service resort I think the dinner menu needs to be expanded on! - The food was good thought...And the breakfast buffet ($12pp) one of the best I've been too../ To the Wyndham hotel: IF you charge a daily resort fee ($12) shouldn't a beach umbrella be included? (I paid an additional $15 per day). Overall the place was very nice,clean and the service and staff would bring us back... Looking to stay here again next year.... 
